'''''Twister''''', also known as '''''Twister: Mother of Charlotte''''' or just '''''Mother of Charlotte''''', is a [[shooting game]] developed by Chris Yates and [[Jon Hare]] for [[Sensible Software]] and published by [[System 3 (software company)|System 3]] for the [[ZX Spectrum]] in 1986. It was originally developed as ''Mother of Harlots'' but was renamed after a controversy regarding the title and sexualized promotion with skimpily dressed dancers at an industry event,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sinclairuser.com/044/gremlin.htm|title=Sinclair User 44 - Gremlin|website=www.sinclairuser.com|access-date=2018-06-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zzap64.co.uk/cgi-bin/displayfeature.pl?featureid=37|title=A Sensible Chat - Part 1|website=www.zzap64.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2018-06-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://amigareviews.leveluphost.com/s_toady.htm|title=Amiga reviews Special: The Toady Awards|last=Janssen|first=Tim|website=amigareviews.leveluphost.com|access-date=2018-06-14|archive-date=2018-06-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614144321/https://amigareviews.leveluphost.com/s_toady.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ziggurat.co.nz/news/2014/2/9/this-month-in-cvg-86|title=This month in... C&VG '86|work=Ziggurat|access-date=2018-06-14|language=en-NZ}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayhem64.co.uk/sensible.htm|title=MayhemUK Commodore 64 archive|website=www.mayhem64.co.uk|access-date=2018-06-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.retro8bitcomputers.co.uk/Content/downloads/magazines/crash/Crash21-Oct85.pdf | title=SHOWMANSHIP? | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327090104/http://www.retro8bitcomputers.co.uk/Content/downloads/magazines/crash/Crash21-Oct85.pdf | archive-date=2019-03-27 | magazine=Crash - ZX Spectrum}}</ref> and a planned [[Commodore 64]] version was never released.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gamesthatwerent.com/gtw64/twister/|title=Twister|date=2012-10-04|work=Games That Weren't|access-date=2018-06-14|language=en-US}}</ref> The game received positive reviews from ''[[Aktueller Software Markt]]'',<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/asm_magazine-1986-07|title=Aktueller Software Markt (ASM) Magazine (July 1986)|date=July 1986|language=de}}</ref> [[Crash (magazine)|''Crash'']],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.zxspectrumreviews.co.uk/review.aspx?gid=6064&rid=5914|title=Sinclair ZX Spectrum Reviews|date=2016-03-26|access-date=2018-06-14|url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326051237/http://www.zxspectrumreviews.co.uk/review.aspx?gid=6064&rid=5914|archive-date=2016-03-26}}</ref> ''[[Sinclair User]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/048/twister.htm|title=Sinclair User 48 - Twister - Mother of Charlotte|date=2011-06-14|access-date=2018-06-14|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110614174929/http://www.sincuser.f9.co.uk/048/twister.htm|archive-date=2011-06-14}}</ref> and ''[[Your Sinclair]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/articles/twister.htm|title=Twister|date=2016-07-08|access-date=2018-06-14|url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160708045049/http://www.ysrnry.co.uk/articles/twister.htm|archive-date=2016-07-08}}</ref>

